SwiSca Twitter Workshop II

Steven Coats

May 2019

Try the Tweepy script

Make a new folder called SwiSca

Download Swisca_script.py to your SwiSca directory.

In a command shell, navigate to the directory and enter python Swisca_script.py

  • You are searching for tweets containing the words darn, gosh, rats, and phooey
  • Tweets will start showing on the screen
  • Our script excludes retweets
  • Use CTRL-X or CTRL-Z to stop the script

Now go to your SwiSca folder. The tweets have been stored in the TweetData folder. A new file is automatically opened every 500 tweets.

Change the search words

  • Open Swisca_script.py in a text editor. Scroll down to the bottom.
  • script
  • Find the line twitterStream.filter(track=["darn","gosh","rats","phooey"])
  • Change the words to others you would like to find
  • Save the file
  • In the command shell, enter python Swisca_script.py again
  • Use CTRL-X or CTRL-Z to stop the script

Search in a particular language

  • In the script, comment out the line you just changed by adding # before it
  • Uncomment the next line by deleting #
  • Save the file and run the script again
  • Now only those tweets containing some Swedish swear words are shown
  • There arent as many people tweeting in real time in Swedish, so it may take a while to get a lot of data

Search in a particular place

  • To search for tweets from a place, we define the bounding box of latitude-longitude coordinates that contain that place
  • Go back to the script and uncomment the first filter
  • We are getting tweets from within the box formed by (longitude:19,latitude:59,longitude:32,latitude:70)
  • This defines a box approximately around Finland

  • Run the script again
  • You should start seeing tweets in Finnish and Russian (among other languages)
  • Note that this method only gets tweets from people who have turned on the Tweet location option in their settings (most users have not)
  • You can check the coordinates of boxes at bboxfinder
  • An additional filtering step can be used to get tweets in a specific language
